   <descr>
      <p>"Soldier Boy" is the name of a song written by Luther Dixon
    and Florence Green. The song was released as a single by The
    Shirelles in 1962 and met with great success, topping the US
    Billboard Hot 100. The song's lyrics are a profession of the
    singer's love for the titular soldier boy in which she promises
    to remain true to him while he's away.</p>
